HEADWORD: Snaphead
<hw>Snap"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hemispherical or
rounded head to a rivet or bolt; also, a swaging tool with a cavity in
its face for forming such a rounded head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

